In this article, President Joe Biden acknowledges the devastating impact of the COVID-19 pandemic, with over 500,000 Americans having lost their lives to the virus. He compares this number to the combined casualties of World War I, World War II, and the Vietnam War. The President emphasizes the need for the nation to remember those who have been lost and calls for unity and healing. As a tribute, he and the First Lady, along with the Vice President and the Second Gentleman, will observe a moment of silence at the White House. President Biden also orders that the flag of the United States be flown at half-staff across the country and at all US embassies and facilities abroad until February 26, 2021, in honor of the victims.